DENGUE - SRI LANKA (SOUTH): ALERT
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
ProMED-mail, a program of ISID
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: 2 Nov 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Australian Broadcasting Corp., Thu 2 Nov 2000 (03:44:34 AEST)[edited]

Sri Lankan schools close because of dengue
-----------------------------------------
Sri Lanka's Health Ministry has ordered 40 schools and a university in the
southern region to close because of an outbreak of dengue fever. The Health
Ministry says 2 people have died from dengue in the past 10 days.
Ruhunu University, the country's largest, and 40 schools in the Matara area
were closed after 115 cases of the mosquito-borne disease were reported.
